pathos_other: stomach: Hematopathology Note (Dr. R. Willim) : Scattered secondary lymphoid follicles with germinal centers are seen. The surrounding lymphocytes are primarily small and are mature appearing. CD20 highlights lymphoid follicles with supporting CD23 positive follicular dendritic cell meshwork and a significant B cell population is not seen away from the follicles. CD3, CD5 and CD43 highlight T cells. CD138 highlights plasma cells which are overall polytypic by kappa and lambda immunostains. The findings are is keeping with chronic gastritis and are not diagnostic of a lymphoproliferative disorder. Clinical and endoscopic correlation is recommended.
